Special assistant to Governor Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State on youth affairs, Olamide Lawal, has reiterated the administration’s commitment to the development of youth in the state. Lawal gave this assurance at the All Progressives Congress (APC) state secretariat in Abeokuta where he addressed some youths in the state under the aegis of the APC Youths League. He said the APC-led government will give more representation to youths in the mission to develop and grow the state. 608 repentant Boko Haram members currently undergoing… Lai Mohammed tasks Nigerians on patriotism, commitment to… Malami’s statement on Amotekun is faulty, Olugbon… Barack Obama eulogises wife as she turns 56 ALSO READ: Ooni honours 100 Nigerian youth leaders Lawal berated the poor representation given the youth population by past governments, adding that the time has come for a new era of good representation. Lawal, who is also the state coordinator of APC Youths League, tasked the youth to support the administration’s ideas and vision, adding that their support is needed to achieve the sustainable feat in office. STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO  WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS FREE